'''Items''' are objects that users can spawn within a world, e.g. toys, tools, gadgets. They can be managed in the [[Inventory]].

== Spawning ==
[[File:Items submenu in Action Menu.png|thumb|Items submenu in [[Action Menu]]|200x200px]]Items can be spawned from the Items submenu in the [[Action Menu]] or from the [[Inventory]]. Users can spawn only one of each item they have. All items spawned by a user are removed after they leave the instance. 

Item spawning or visibility can be affected by being:

* Disabled by the world.
* Disabled by a group moderator in a group instance (but can't be forced on if disabled by the world).
* Hidden locally by an individual user.

== Types ==
[[File:THE_REFERENCE_CUBE_item_original.png|thumb|200x200px|A image of "THE REFERENCE CUBE" item.]]
While offering a range of different features, items can be artificially grouped by their properties:

'''Placeable items'''

A placeable item can be placed on a floor in a world. It cannot be spawned on walls, ceilings or on other users.

'''Pickup items'''

A pickupable item can be grabbed by the user and sometimes other users too.

'''Consumable items'''

A consumable item gets destroyed after being placed and activated. It can stack in the inventory.

'''Companion'''

A pet-type item that follows the user around. These items have a distinct "Companion" label in the [[Special:MyLanguage/Shop|Shop]].

== Worlds ==
''See also [https://creators.vrchat.com/worlds/items Items in Udon Worlds] for more detailed information.''

==== Content settings ====
World creators can disable items in the "Default Content Settings" section by editing a world on the website, in case they are causing issues or are undesirable.

==== Unity layer ====
''See also [https://creators.vrchat.com/worlds/layers/ Unity Layers in VRChat] for more detailed information.''

A dedicated "Item" Unity layer is where items spawn. Previously named "reserved3" in older SDK versions.

